text: Vojtěch Plát (born 23 January 1994) is a Czech chess grandmaster. He won the Czech Chess Championship in 2016. ==Chess career== Born in 1994, Plát earned his international master title in 2009 and his grandmaster title in 2017.2nd quarter Presidential Board Meeting 2017 by written resolution FIDE He won the Czech Chess Championship in 2016. In 2019, he won the O Losinskeho Kapra in Kouty nad Desnou, Czech Republic with a score of 8/9 points. He is the No. 10 ranked Czech player as of July 2020. ==References== ==External links== * * Category:1994 births Category:Living people Category:Chess grandmasters Category:Czech chess players Category:Sportspeople from Ostrava
